<li>2018: Turner's <i><a href="/wiki/Private_Dancer" title="Private Dancer">Private Dancer</a></i> album appeared on <i><a href="/wiki/Rolling_Stone" title="Rolling Stone">Rolling Stone</a>'</i>s list of the 100 Best Albums of the 1980s and was also included in the book <i><a href="/wiki/1001_Albums_You_Must_Hear_Before_You_Die" title="1001 Albums You Must Hear Before You Die">1001 Albums You Must Hear Before You Die</a></i>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-392" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-392"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>391<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2018:&#160;Billboard&#160;ranked Turner at number 37 on their Top 60 Female Artists of All-Time list.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-393" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-393"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>392<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2019: Turner was inducted into the <a href="/wiki/Memphis_Music_Hall_of_Fame" title="Memphis Music Hall of Fame">Memphis Music Hall of Fame</a>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-394" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-394"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>393<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2020: Turner was ranked as one of the 50 greatest voices of the 80s by <a href="/wiki/MTV" title="MTV">MTV</a>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-395" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-395"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>394<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2020: <i>Billboard</i> included Turner on its list of the 100 Greatest Music Video Artists of All Time.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-396" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-396"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>395<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2020: <i><a href="/wiki/Private_Dancer" title="Private Dancer">Private Dancer</a></i> was added to the <a href="/wiki/National_Recording_Registry" title="National Recording Registry">National Recording Registry</a> at the <a href="/wiki/Library_of_Congress" title="Library of Congress">Library of Congress</a>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-397" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-397"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>396<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2021: Turner became a two-time Rock and Roll Hall of Fame inductee.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-NPR-2021&#95;398-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NPR-2021-398"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>397<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2021: Turner received an honorary doctorate for her "unique musical and artistic life's work" from the Philosophical and Historical Faculty of the <a href="/wiki/University_of_Bern" title="University of Bern">University of Bern</a>.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-399" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-399"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>398<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2023: <i>Rolling Stone</i> ranked Turner number 55 on their list of the 200 Greatest Singers of All Time.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-400" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-400"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>399<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2023: The song "What's Love Got to Do With It" appeared on <i>Billboard</i><span class="nowrap" style="padding-left:0.1em;">&#39;s</span> list of the 500 best pop songs of all time.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-401" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-401"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>400<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2023–2024:&#160;<a href="/wiki/Smooth_Radio_(2014)" class="mw-redirect" title="Smooth Radio (2014)">Smooth Radio</a>&#160;ranked Turner number 8 on their list of the top music icons of all time.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-402" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-402"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>401<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2025: <a href="/wiki/Forbes" title="Forbes">Forbes</a> ranked her number 9 on The 50 Black Female Singers With Incredible Vocals List.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-403" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-403"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>402<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> and number five on their list of the best female singers of the 80s.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-404" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-404"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>403<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
<li>2025: Turner was selected for induction into the National Rhythm and Blues Hall of Fame.<sup id="cite&#95;ref-R&amp;B25&#95;344-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-R&amp;B25-344"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>343<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup></li>
